      "name": "Mindless (Ex)",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/svg/mystery-man.svg",
      "data": {
        "description": {
          "chat": "",
          "gmnotes": "",
          "short": "",
          "value": "<p>The creature has no Intelligence score or modifier and is immune to @Compendium[sfrpg.rules.PqV3OCbUTyk2upPD]{Mind-affecting effects}. Any DCs or other statistics that rely on an Intelligence score treat the creature as having a score of 10(+0).</p>\n<p><em>Format</em>: <strong>Other Abilities</strong> mindless.</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListRulesAll_ctl34_LabelName\"><em>Guidelines</em>: Mindless creatures usually have fewer good skills and no master skills. Their skills should be based on inborn abilities, since they&rsquo;re incapable of training.</span></p>",
