    {
      "_id": "dcqtIv05m0nX7eRP",
      "name": "Regeneration 5 (acid)",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/svg/mystery-man.svg",
      "data": {
        "description": {
          "chat": "",
          "gmnotes": "",
          "short": "",
          "value": "<p>The creature regains Hit Points at the start of its turn, as with fast healing, but it can&rsquo;t die as long as its regeneration is still functioning (although creatures with regeneration still fall @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.lf8pbezocjYIvR9y]{Unconscious} when their Hit Points reach 0). Certain attacks, typically those that deal acid or fire damage, cause a creature&rsquo;s regeneration to stop functioning for 1 round. During this round, the creature doesn&rsquo;t regain Hit Points and can die normally. The creature&rsquo;s stat block describes the types of damage that suppress the regeneration.</p>\n<p>Regeneration doesn&rsquo;t restore Hit Points lost from starvation, thirst, or suffocation. Creatures with regeneration can regrow lost portions of their bodies and can reattach severed body parts if they are recovered within 1 hour of severing. Severed parts that aren&rsquo;t reattached wither and decompose normally.</p>\n<p>A creature usually must have a Constitution score or modifier to have this ability.</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListRulesAll_ctl44_LabelName\"><em>Format</em>: <strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> regeneration 5 (acid).</span></p>",
          "unidentified": ""
        },
        "source": "AA1 pg. 156",
